      <hedline>
        <hl1>Tech 2010</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Mildred M Jeffrey letter on special June 11 issue on millennium technology suggests issue on future of arts, education, religion, philosophy and social sciences</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>According to your tech issue, life in the future will be more fulfilling because of time and effort saved by gadgets and gee-whiz electronic ware. What will people do with the saved time and energy? Will they be more polite? Will they be more compassionate?</p>
        <p>To comfort those of us who are not seduced by technology, might I suggest that you do an issue about the future of the arts, education, religion, philosophy and the social sciences? Perhaps the seeds of hope for the survival of courtesy and the recognition of familial and civic responsibility may be found in these fields.</p>
        <p>Mildred M. Jeffrey</p>
        <p>Boston</p>
      </block>
